President Obama called President Aquino of the Philippines to offer condolences for the lives lost and damage caused by Super Typhoon Haiyan/Yolanda. The President directed the Administration to provide swift and coordinated assistance to help the Filipino people. They discussed the need for a quick assessment of American resources that would be most helpful in the recovery effort. The United States will continue to work with the Philippines to deliver aid as quickly as possible. President Obama expressed the thoughts and prayers of the American people for those affected by the storm.